<item>
            <title>[OAK-428] Binaries might get removed by garbage collection while still referenced</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-428</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/jackrabbit/oak/trunk/oak-mk-api/src/main/java/org/apache/jackrabbit/mk/api/MicroKernel.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Microkernel contract&lt;/a&gt; specifies a specific format for references to binaries: &quot;:blobId:&amp;lt;blobId&amp;gt;&quot;. Currently oak-core uses a different format and thus risks premature garbage collection of such binaries.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12615133">OAK-428</key>
            <summary>Binaries might get removed by garbage collection while still referenced</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="mduerig">Michael D&#252;rig</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="mduerig">Michael D&#252;rig</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Wed, 7 Nov 2012 10:43:08 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 8 Oct 2019 15:21:16 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 13 Nov 2012 12:21:12 +0000</resolved>
                                                    <fixVersion>0.6</fixVersion>
                                    <component>core</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13493226" author="mduerig" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2012 14:42:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Using &quot;:blobId:&quot; instead of &quot;bin:&quot; to prefix binaries leads to special casing in how the type codes are interpreted. Worse, it might break &lt;tt&gt;PrefixContentIndex&lt;/tt&gt; wrt. to the changes from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-182&quot; title=&quot;Support for &amp;quot;invisible&amp;quot; internal content&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-182&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-182&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13493228" author="mduerig" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2012 14:44:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch changes the prefix from &quot;bin:&quot; to &quot;:blobId&quot;. All test cases pass. However I suspect &lt;tt&gt;PrefixContentIndex&lt;/tt&gt; is now broken for binary properties. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thomasm&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thomasm&quot;&gt;thomasm&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=alexparvulescu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;alexparvulescu&quot;&gt;alexparvulescu&lt;/a&gt; could you check and add a test case before we proceed with the patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13495252" author="tmueller" created="Mon, 12 Nov 2012 13:32:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks! &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Just to avoid confusion) I think the new prefix is &quot;:blobId:&quot; not &quot;:blobId&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch seems to contain a large IntelliJ specific header. I guess I can ignore it?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The PrefixContentIndex will most likely anyway have to be re-written (to use the oak-core classes and not the MicroKernel API), so I don&apos;t worry too much about it at the moment, but thanks for the heads-up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13496134" author="mduerig" created="Tue, 13 Nov 2012 12:05:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, so I&apos;ll apply the patch then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13496140" author="mduerig" created="Tue, 13 Nov 2012 12:21:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed at revision 1408693&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
